[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
CONFIGURATION:
-------------
The configuration file can be found (or created) at the following path:
  %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/local.json
The default values are available in the default.json configuration file,
which is available in the folders above. Please do not edit the contents of the
default.json file directly. The default values will be restored each time you
upgrade Document Server to a new version and all your changes will be lost. 

1. Enable services at startup in the /etc/rc.conf file:
  nginx_enable="YES"
  supervisord_enable="YES"

  Optionally in case of a jail with local IP and no internet access:
    update /etc/hosts in order to resolve your nextcloud server to its local IP

2. Set up supervisord in order to execute documentserver services:
  - let supervisord.conf load files contained in this directory by adding to
    %%PREFIX%%/etc/supervisord.conf:
[include]
files = %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/supervisor/*.conf

  - start supervisord:
    # service supervisord start

3. Set up nginx:
  - For HTTP include the following in your %%PREFIX%%/etc/nginx/nginx.conf file:
      include %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/nginx/ds.conf;

NOTE: documentserver-update-securelink.sh will only update ./nginx/ds.conf and local.json under %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/!
  - run documentserver-update-securelink.sh once for creating a verysecretstring

  - start nginx:
    # service nginx start

4. Install OnlyOffice plugins (you'll need internet):
   # %%PREFIX%%/bin/documentserver-pluginsmanager.sh --update=%%PREFIX%%/www/onlyoffice/documentserver/sdkjs-plugins/plugin-list-default.json

5. Set up Onlyoffice with Nextcloud, if desired:
  - JWT is mandated within Onlyoffice Nextcloud app, requiring edits to %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/local.json:
      In the token:enable section, set the browser, request:inbox and request:outbox objects to "true"

  - create a secure JWT secret (Base64 avoids issues with JSON/PHP character escaping)
    # openssl rand -base64 48

  - store the JWT secret in %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/local.json:
      In the services:Coauthoring:secret section, enter the JWT secret in the browser, inbox, outbox and session objects

  - restart Onlyoffice:
    # service supervisord restart

  - specify the JWT secret in the Nextcloud administrative configuration for Onlyoffice app

  - see the following for more info:
      https://api.onlyoffice.com/editors/nextcloud

8. Enjoy.
EOM
}
{ type: upgrade
  maximum_version: 7.1.0.215
  message: <<EOM
If you are upgrading onlyoffice-documentserver from a version prior to 7.1.0.215,
you need to update the database schema:
  For PostgreSQL:
    psql -U postgres -d onlyoffice -f %%WWWDIR%%/documentserver/server/schema/postgresql/upgrade/upgradev710.sql
  For MySQL:
    mysql -u onlyoffice -D onlyoffice -p < %%WWWDIR%%/documentserver/server/schema/mysql/upgrade/upgradev710.sql
EOM
}
{ type: upgrade
  minimum_version: 7.1.0.215
  maximum_version: 7.2.1.34
  message: <<EOM
If you are upgrading onlyoffice-documentserver from a version prior to 7.2.1.34,
you need to update the database schema:
  For PostgreSQL:
    psql -U postgres -d onlyoffice -f %%WWWDIR%%/documentserver/server/schema/postgresql/upgrade/upgradev720.sql
  For MySQL:
    mysql -u onlyoffice -D onlyoffice -p < %%WWWDIR%%/documentserver/server/schema/mysql/upgrade/upgradev720.sql
EOM
}
{ type: upgrade
  minimum_version: 9.1.0
  maximum_version: 9.1.0_1
  message: <<EOM
NOTICE: The Admin Panel has been made closed source as of version 9.3.0.
It is no longer included in the community edition and is now only available
in the Developer and Enterprise editions of ONLYOFFICE Docs.

Attempts to access the Admin Panel URL (http://host/admin) will fail.
All configuration remains fully available through %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/local.json
as before, with no loss of functionality for the community edition.

You may safely remove any Admin Panel logs and configuration files:
  # rm -rf /var/log/onlyoffice/documentserver/adminpanel
  # rm -f %%ETCDIR%%/documentserver/supervisor/adminpanel.conf
EOM
}
{ type: upgrade
  maximum_version: 9.4.0
  message: <<EOM
NOTICE: As of ONLYOFFICE Docs 9.4.0, the upstream Community Edition no
longer supports PostgreSQL, MySQL, or RabbitMQ. These capabilities
remain available only in the Developer and Enterprise editions.

If upgrading from a version prior to 9.4.0, net/rabbitmq and any
database client packages used solely by ONLYOFFICE Docs may be removed.
After verifying proper operation, any database previously dedicated to
ONLYOFFICE Docs may be archived and deleted.
EOM
}
]
